s can be seen to be reversed and the dynamics of flexible polymers be\nreached. However, for example, polymers used in translocation experiments of\nDNA, are elastically so short, that the finite-length dynamics outlined here\napplies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Feb 2018 13:10:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 23 Feb 2018 12:15:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-27"}
